@startuml
title HTTP request error handling flow\nPhase 4 - after current-principal HTTP dependency

hide footbox
autonumber

actor "Client\nexternal caller" as Client

box "Runtime" #LightGray
participant "Uvicorn\nASGI server" as Uvicorn
participant "FastAPI app\ninterfaces/http/app.py" as FastAPI
end box

box "HTTP interface layer" #AliceBlue
participant "Router / endpoint\ninterfaces/http/routers/*.py" as Router
participant "HTTP dependencies\ninterfaces/http/dependencies/*.py" as Dependencies
participant "Security dependency\ninterfaces/http/dependencies/security.py" as SecurityDependency
participant "Error handlers\ninterfaces/http/error_handlers.py" as ErrorHandlers
participant "_build_error_response()\ninterfaces/http/error_handlers.py" as ErrorBuilder
participant "Error schemas\ninterfaces/http/schemas/errors.py" as ErrorSchemas
participant "JSONResponse\nfastapi.responses" as JsonResponse
end box

box "Application / domain / infrastructure" #HoneyDew
participant "JwtTokenVerifier\ninfrastructure/security/jwt_token_verifier.py" as Verifier
participant "Use case / domain /\ninfrastructure adapter" as Backend
end box

participant "Logger\nlogging" as Logger


note over FastAPI, ErrorHandlers
Application startup happens before requests:

create_app()
  -> register_exception_handlers(app)

This registers which handler FastAPI must call
for each known exception type.

The registration is application-scoped,
not request-scoped.
end note


Client -> Uvicorn: HTTP request
Uvicorn -> FastAPI: ASGI request
FastAPI -> Router: Match route
Router -> Dependencies: Resolve dependencies needed by endpoint

alt Protected endpoint needs authentication

    Dependencies -> SecurityDependency: get_current_principal()

    SecurityDependency -> SecurityDependency: HTTPBearer(auto_error=False)

    alt Missing Authorization header or wrong scheme

        note right of SecurityDependency
        Examples:

        No Authorization header

        Authorization: Basic abc123
        end note

        SecurityDependency -> SecurityDependency: raise AuthenticationError
        SecurityDependency --> FastAPI: exception propagates

        FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_authentication_error(request, exc)
        ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=401\ncode=unauthorized\nmessage=generic\nheaders={WWW-Authenticate: Bearer}
        ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
        ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
        ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
        JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
        ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 401 Unauthorized
        FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 401 + envelope + WWW-Authenticate
        Uvicorn --> Client: authentication error response

    else Bearer token is present

        SecurityDependency -> Verifier: verify(raw_token)

        alt Token is invalid

            note right of Verifier
            Examples:

            - malformed JWT
            - invalid signature
            - expired token
            - wrong issuer
            - wrong audience
            - missing required claim
            - invalid claim shape
            end note

            Verifier --> SecurityDependency: TokenVerificationError

            note right of SecurityDependency
            The technical token error is translated
            into a generic HTTP authentication error.

            Client does not receive the internal reason.
            end note

            SecurityDependency -> SecurityDependency: raise AuthenticationError
            SecurityDependency --> FastAPI: exception propagates

            FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_authentication_error(request, exc)
            ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=401\ncode=unauthorized\nmessage=generic\nheaders={WWW-Authenticate: Bearer}
            ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
            ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
            ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
            JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
            ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 401 Unauthorized
            FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 401 + envelope + WWW-Authenticate
            Uvicorn --> Client: authentication error response

        else Verifier configuration is invalid

            note right of Verifier
            Examples:

            - JWT secret is missing
            - JWT secret is too short

            This is a server configuration problem,
            not a client credential problem.
            end note

            Verifier --> SecurityDependency: TokenVerifierConfigurationError

            note right of SecurityDependency
            get_current_principal()
            does not catch this exception.
            end note

            SecurityDependency --> FastAPI: exception propagates

            FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_token_verifier_configuration_error(request, exc)
            ErrorHandlers -> Logger: logger.error(real internal reason)
            Logger --> ErrorHandlers: logged
            ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=500\ncode=internal_server_error\nmessage=generic
            ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
            ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
            ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
            JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
            ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 500 Internal Server Error
            FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 500 + generic envelope
            Uvicorn --> Client: internal server error response

        else Token is valid

            Verifier --> SecurityDependency: VerifiedJwtClaims
            SecurityDependency -> SecurityDependency: Create CurrentPrincipal
            SecurityDependency --> Dependencies: CurrentPrincipal

        end

    end

else Public endpoint

    note right of Dependencies
    Example:

    GET /health

    No authentication dependency is executed.
    end note

end


alt Dependencies completed successfully

    Dependencies --> Router: dependency values
    Router -> Backend: execute endpoint/use-case flow

    alt Application validation fails

        Backend --> FastAPI: ApplicationValidationError
        FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_application_validation_error(request, exc)
        ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=400\ncode=validation_error\nmessage=exc.message\nfield=exc.field
        ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
        ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
        ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
        JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
        ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 400 Bad Request
        FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 400 + validation envelope
        Uvicorn --> Client: validation error response

    else Domain validation fails

        Backend --> FastAPI: DomainValidationError
        FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_domain_validation_error(request, exc)
        ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=400\ncode=validation_error\nmessage=exc.message\nfield=exc.field
        ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
        ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
        ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
        JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
        ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 400 Bad Request
        FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 400 + validation envelope
        Uvicorn --> Client: domain validation error response

    else Resource is not found

        Backend --> FastAPI: ApplicationNotFoundError
        FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_application_not_found_error(request, exc)
        ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=404\ncode=not_found\nmessage=exc.message\nresource=exc.resource\nidentifier=exc.identifier
        ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
        ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
        ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
        JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
        ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 404 Not Found
        FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 404 + not-found envelope
        Uvicorn --> Client: not-found response

    else Unexpected error

        Backend --> FastAPI: Exception
        FastAPI -> ErrorHandlers: handle_unexpected_error(request, exc)
        ErrorHandlers -> Logger: logger.exception(...)\nwith traceback
        Logger --> ErrorHandlers: logged
        ErrorHandlers -> ErrorBuilder: status=500\ncode=internal_server_error\nmessage=generic
        ErrorBuilder -> ErrorSchemas: ApiError + ApiErrorResponse
        ErrorSchemas --> ErrorBuilder: serialized envelope
        ErrorBuilder -> JsonResponse: create JSONResponse
        JsonResponse --> ErrorHandlers: response
        ErrorHandlers --> FastAPI: 500 Internal Server Error
        FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 500 + generic envelope
        Uvicorn --> Client: internal server error response

    else No error

        Backend --> Router: application result
        Router --> FastAPI: successful response body
        FastAPI --> Uvicorn: 2xx response
        Uvicorn --> Client: successful response

    end

end

note over ErrorBuilder, ErrorSchemas
All custom handled errors use the same envelope:

{
  "error": {
    "code": "...",
    "message": "...",
    "field": null,
    "resource": null,
    "identifier": null
  }
}
end note

@enduml
